FEDERAL Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN) has moved its headquarters to Abuja in compliance with the Federal Ministry of Aviation’s directive that agencies in the sector relocate their headquarters to Abuja. General Manager, Public Affairs, Mrs Henrietta Yakubu made this known yesterday in a statement. The movement, she said, was aimed at ensuring operational efficiency, while  improving the quality of service delivery to our esteemed customers. Already, the Managing Director, Capt. Rabiu Yadudu, directors and other critical  staff members of the Authority, Mrs Yakubu said, had since relocated to the new FAAN headquarters.